<aigx-protocol>
  <read-first>Open .aigx/files.aigx and find the &lt;file&gt; entry for EACH file you will edit - it lists that file's forbidden/allowed imports, schema, data boundary and gotchas. Obey its &lt;forbid pri="CRIT"&gt; and satisfy every id in its &lt;check&gt; before finishing.</read-first>
  <step n="1">Read the per-concern rule files in .aigx/ that the task touches.</step>
  <step n="2">Read .aigx/files.aigx for the per-file boundaries of files you edit.</step>
  <step n="3">Schema-first (ARCH-5); failing test first (TEST-1); minimal change, local blast radius.</step>
  <step n="4">Run gates; verify each file's &lt;check&gt; ids hold.</step>
</aigx-protocol>
